      "name": "K8s - Pod Failure Detected",
      "description": "This alert is triggered when a pod in a Kubernetes cluster enters a `Failed` state, indicating that it has terminated unexpectedly and cannot be restarted. Pod failures can disrupt workloads and reduce application availability if not addressed promptly. \nAction: Investigate the failed pod by checking its logs, Kubernetes events, and associated resources. Common causes of pod failure include:\n      - Application crashes due to unhandled exceptions or runtime errors\n      - Misconfigured environment variables, secrets, or volumes\n      - Insufficient resources (e.g., CPU, memory)\n      - Failed probes (liveness or readiness)\n    Take corrective actions, such as fixing the root cause, redeploying the pod, or increasing resource limits, to restore normal operations.",
